  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen factors are assessed; the Use Error factor is recorded as not-assessed on the grounds that operator interaction with the simulation software is claimed to be irrelevant to the COU — a rationale that does not satisfy the not-applicable encoding requirement and therefore leaves a material gap at MRL 3.",
