      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation performed across three systematically refined meshes (4.1M, 12.3M, 36.9M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index is 1.8%, well within the 5% threshold. Discretization error quantified at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate 3–6 L/min, rotational speed 2000–3500 RPM, blood temperature 37°C, hematocrit 33%) are documented and traceable to ASTM F1841 and ISO 10993-4 protocols. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error is 8.2% with maximum deviation 14.1%. Statistical comparison using Bland-Altman analysis confirms acceptable agreement. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — relative hemolysis index (RH) computed from shear stress history integration — directly maps to the clinical endpoint of plasma-free hemoglobin elevation. Linkage between computational QoI and clinical metric is documented. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted on the same FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry at operating conditions spanning the COU envelope. Fluid properties (bovine blood surrogate) and boundary conditions are representative of CPB clinical use. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence monitored via scaled residuals (all below 1e-5) and global mass and momentum imbalances (below 0.01%). Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Solver error contribution to QoI uncertainty estimated at less than 0.5%. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that use error does not apply to this context of use because the CFD simulation is executed by a single trained analyst following a fixed simulation protocol, and no interactive operator decisions affect the hemolysis QoI during a production run. Accordingly, no formal use-error assessment was conducted and no required or achieved levels are assigned. Note: this determination was recorded as 'not-assessed' rather than 'not-applicable' because the formal exclusion argument has not been reviewed by an independent auditor, leaving a material unassessed gap at MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "The power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is compared against three alternative constitutive forms (Taskin, Zhang, Arora). Sensitivity of RH predictions to model-form choice is quantified; the selected model shows lowest bias against the experimental dataset. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry tolerances ±0.05 mm, blood viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s ±10%, inlet velocity profiles from PIV measurements) are documented with uncertainty bounds. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis identifies viscosity and inlet turbulence intensity as dominant inputs. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments used three independently fabricated pump specimens from the same manufacturing lot. Inter-specimen variability in NIH measurements was 6.3% (CV), providing a basis for assessing geometric manufacturing variability. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 3.",
      "rationale": "Dimensional analysis confirms dynamic similarity between validation experiments and COU operating conditions. Reynolds number (Re = 4800–9200) and Stokes number ranges overlap between bench tests and clinical operating envelope. Equivalency documented at Gradation 2."
